@startuml

title University Registration System - Class Diagram

class Student {
  +id: int
  +fullName: string
  +email: string
}

class Course {
  +id: int
  +title: string
  +capacity: int
}

class Professor {
  +id: int
  +fullName: string
  +department: string
}

class Enrollment {
  +id: int
  +enrollmentDate: date
  +status: string
}

Professor "1" -- "0..*" Course : Association / teaches

Student "1" *-- "0..*" Enrollment : Composition / has

Course "1" o-- "0..*" Enrollment : Aggregation / contains

note right of Professor
A professor can teach many courses.
Professor and Course can exist independently.
end note

note left of Student
A student owns enrollment records.
If the student is removed, related enrollments
should also be removed.
end note

note right of Course
A course can contain many enrollments.
However, the course can exist even without enrollments.
end note

@enduml
